            <p class="text-center"><b>DEALING PROCEDURE</b></p>
            <p><span class="text-gray">The dealing procedure of each game shall be as follows:</span></p>
            <p><span class="text-gray"><i class="fa-solid fa-check text-secondary me-3"></i> The Dealer shall   refer to   the   Dealer Dashboard (with attached camera) before and after the game for instruction or guidance.</span></p>
            <p><span class="text-gray"><i class="fa-solid fa-check text-secondary me-3"></i> Accepting of bets through remote gaming platforms ensues when the status on the Dealer Dashboard reads "OPEN".</span></p>
            <p><span class="text-gray"><i class="fa-solid fa-check text-secondary me-3"></i> Player bets on GOLD or SILVER, whether on regular bet and/or side bet options. Once a player clicks his/her choice, the bet amount option pops up, enters preset chip denominations or manually key-in amount then clicks "PLACE BET," otherwise "CANCEL".</span></p>
            <p><span class="text-gray"><i class="fa-solid fa-check text-secondary me-3"></i> A confirmation button shall appear for the player to confirm the selected bet option and amount by clicking "Yes", otherwise "No".</span></p>
            <p><span class="text-gray"><i class="fa-solid fa-check text-secondary me-3"></i> The system timer starts until the allotted period for betting ends. System automatically disables all access for betting and changes the status to "CLOSED".</span></p>
            <p><span class="text-gray"><i class="fa-solid fa-check text-secondary me-3"></i> ⦁	At the conclusion of betting, the Dealer shall start with the dealing procedure in the following sequence:</span></p>
            <p>
                <span class="text-gray">
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-check text-secondary me-3"></i>
                    The Dealer shall pick up the ball inside the canister. <br> <br>

                    Upon retrieval, the Dealer shall immediately spin the ball in any way on top of the transparent funnel, wait to drop and settle onthe wheel. <br> <br>

                    After checking the winning color and number, the Dealer shall declare/ encode the winning outcome in the Dealer's Tablet for theGame Validator's confirmation. <br> <br>

                    Dealer shall perform this cycle continuously during his stint until he is relieved by another Dealer, the last deal has been announced, or theequipment needs to undergo maintenance. <br> <br>
                </span>
            </p>
            <p><span class="text-gray"><i class="fa-solid fa-check text-secondary me-3"></i> The Dealer shall replace the ball every shift in a different color. But in case of a damaged ball, such as dents or breakage, within the shift, the same color ofball shall be used.</span></p>

            <p class="text-center"><b>IRREGULARITIES</b></p>
            <p><span class="text-gray"><i class="fa-solid fa-exclamation text-warning me-3"></i> The attention of the Pit Supervisor (PS) must be called on all irregularities made or observed.</span></p>
            <p><span class="text-gray"><i class="fa-solid fa-exclamation text-warning me-3"></i> Should the ping-pong/rubber ball become damaged, such as deformed, cracked, or dented, the Dealer shall immediately inform the PS forreplacement of the said ball. The game result shall be considered valid if the damage, deformity, crack, or dent is detected only during play or as soon as the ball has settled on the wheel, provided the defective ball remains intact. The damaged ball must be replaced immediately after the game.</span></p>
            <p><span class="text-gray"><i class="fa-solid fa-exclamation text-warning me-3"></i> Should the ball break, split, or fragment into two or more pieces during play, the game result is automatically deemed invalid, and the damaged ball must be replaced immediately. The Dealer must then throw the replacement ball again regardless of where the split parts of the original ball may have settled.</span></p>
